"principal arteries brain and spinal column, open approach-part a. this class includes one or more of 17 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the principal arteries of the brain and spinal column with open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 03.. . "
"principal arteries brain and spinal column, open approach-part a. this class includes one or more of 17 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the principal arteries of the brain and spinal column with open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 03.. restriction of left vertebral artery,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to restriction of left vertebral artery,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 03vq0zz. "
"principal arteries brain and spinal column, open approach-part a. this class includes one or more of 17 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the principal arteries of the brain and spinal column with open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 03.. restriction of left vertebral artery with intraluminal device,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to restriction of left vertebral artery with intraluminal device,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 03vq0dz. "

"

"principal arteries chest or thorax, open approach-part a. this class includes one or more of 17 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the principal arteries of the chest or thorax with open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 03.. reposition left subclavian artery,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to reposition left subclavian artery,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 03s40zz. "

"principal arteries chest or thorax, percutaneous endoscopic approach-part a. this class includes one or more of 17 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the principal arteries of the chest or thorax with percutaneous endoscopic approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 03.. occlusion of left subclavian artery,  percutaneous endoscopic approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to occlusion of left subclavian artery,  percutaneous endoscopic approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 03l44zz. "

"principal arteries head and neck, open approach-part b. this class includes one or more of 17 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the principal arteries of the head and neck with open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 03.. occlusion of right external carotid artery with intraluminal device,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to occlusion of right external carotid artery with intraluminal device,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 03lm0dz. "

"principal arteries head and neck, percutaneous approach-part b. this class includes one or more of 17 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the principal arteries of the head and neck with percutaneous approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 03.. occlusion of left common carotid artery with intraluminal device,  percutaneous approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to occlusion of left common carotid artery with intraluminal device,  percutaneous approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 03lj3dz. "

"principal arteries upper extremities, open approach-part b. this class includes one or more of 17 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the principal arteries of the upper extremities with open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 03.. occlusion of right hand artery with intraluminal device,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to occlusion of right hand artery with intraluminal device,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 03ld0dz. "

"
